QuakeCode – Privacy Policy
Effective Date: July 21, 2025
This Privacy Policy applies to the latest version of QuakeCode, our mobile application dedicated to AI-powered earthquake prediction. It explains how we collect, use, store, and protect user data. By using QuakeCode, you agree to the practices described below.
1. Information We Collect
QuakeCode may collect the following types of information:
 Device Information: Device model, operating system version, and general system performance data to ensure compatibility, security, and proper functionality.
 Location Data: Only collected with your explicit consent, for delivering location-specific earthquake predictions and alerts.
 App Usage Data: Data on how you use the app, including frequency, duration, and feature interactions, to help us improve the app.
 User Feedback and Reports: Voluntary input from users, such as felt earthquake reports or feedback about the app’s functionality.
2. How We Use Your Data
We use collected data to:
 Enhance the accuracy and performance of our earthquake prediction algorithms.
 Provide personalized, location-based alerts and insights (if location permission is granted).
 Improve and customize your user experience.
 Identify and resolve technical issues or bugs.
 Support anonymized scientific research aimed at improving earthquake forecasting models.
3. Data Sharing
 No Personal Data Sharing: We do not sell, rent, or share your personal data with advertisers or third parties for commercial purposes.
 Research Collaboration: We may share anonymized, aggregated data with academic and scientific partners to contribute to earthquake science and AI model development.
4. Data Storage and Deletion
 Secure Storage: Your data is stored using industry-standard encryption and security practices to prevent unauthorized access or misuse.
 Local Data: Uninstalling the app will automatically delete all data stored locally on your device.
 Server Data: You may request the permanent deletion of any data stored on our servers by contacting us.
5. Your Privacy Rights
As a QuakeCode user, you have the right to:
 Know what data we collect and how we use it.
 Request access to, correction of, or deletion of your personal data.
 Revoke location permissions at any time through your device settings.
 Contact us regarding any privacy-related questions or concerns.
6. Changes to This Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy to reflect changes in technology, regulations, or app features. Significant updates will be communicated through the app or official channels.
7. Contact Us
If you have questions, requests, or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy or your data, please contact:
